This '''swoop biker''' rode a [[Flare-S swoop/Legends|Flare-S swoop]] in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] and startled a [[Ronto/Legends|ronto]] and its [[Jawa/Legends|Jawa]] riders when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was about to meet [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] in the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]].<ref name="ANHSE">{{Film|IV}} {{C|Special Edition}}</ref> He was a [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] and likely part of a [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] [[Swoop gang/Legends|swoop gang]]. He wore a tall [[shock-helmet]].<ref name="CCG" />

==Behind the scenes==
Concept art of this rider drawn by [[TyRuben Ellingson]]<ref name="SE Widevision 31">{{Topps|set=1997 Topps Star Wars Special Edition Widevision|cardname=#31 Int. Mos Eisley&mdash;Spaceport&mdash;Docking Bay 94|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/73004/cid/5259678/1997-Topps-Star-Wars-Special-Edition-Widevision-Hobby-14-Rearing-Ronto}}</ref> showed a complete detailed view of the character, though he can only be glimpsed briefly in the [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Edition]] of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. One piece shows two riders instead of one, both wearing similar outfits.<ref name="6 Fascinating">{{SW|url=news/6-fascinating-behind-the-scenes-concepts-from-the-star-wars-trilogy-special-edition|text=6 Fascinating Behind-the-Scenes Concepts from The ''Star Wars'' Trilogy Special Edition|nolive=1}}</ref> This character has not received an official name, but [[Industrial Light & Magic|ILM]] staff nicknamed him "Bubba Fett."<ref name="SE Widevision 31" />

